Class OrganizationAccountStoreMappings

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.stormpath.sdk.organization.OrganizationAccountStoreMappings

  • public final class OrganizationAccountStoreMappings
extends Object
    Static utility/helper methods for working with OrganizationAccountStoreMapping resources. Most methods are factory methods used for forming OrganizationAccountStoreMapping-specific fluent DSL queries. for example: 
     OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.criteria()
     .withOrganization()
     .offsetBy(50)
     .limitTo(25));
    or 
     OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.where(OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.listIndex().eq(3))
     .withAccountStore()
    or, if using static imports: 
     import static com.stormpath.sdk.organization.OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.*;

 ...

     .withOrganization()
     .offsetBy(50)
     .limitTo(25));
    or

      • criteria

        public static OrganizationAccountStoreMappingCriteria criteria()
        Returns a new OrganizationAccountStoreMappingCriteria instance to use to formulate a query.

        Note that it is usually more common to use the where method instead of this one as the where method usually lends to better readability. For example: 

         OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.criteria().add(OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.listIndex().eq(8))...
        versus: 
         OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.where(OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.listIndex().eq(8))...
        or when using static imports: 
         where(listIndex().eq(8))...
        While all three statements are equivalent, the second and third examples are shorter and probably more readable.
        Returns:
        a new OrganizationAccountStoreMappingCriteria instance to use to formulate an OrganizationAccountStoreMapping query.

      • listIndex

        public static EqualsExpressionFactory listIndex()
        Creates a new EqualsExpressionFactory instance reflecting the OrganizationAccountStoreMapping listIndex property, to be used to construct a listIndex Criterion when building an OrganizationAccountStoreMappingCriteria query. For example: 
         OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.where(OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.listIndex().eq(12);
        The above example invokes the returned factory's eq() method. This produces a listIndex-specific Criterion which is added to the criteria query (via the where method). For example, the following code is equivalent: 
         OrganizationAccountStoreMappingCriteria criteria = OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.criteria();
 EqualsExpressionFactory listIndexExpressionFactory = OrganizationAccountStoreMappings.listIndex();
 Criterion listIndexEqualsTen = listIndexExpressionFactory.eq(10);
 criteria.add(listIndexEqualsEnabled);
        The first code example is clearly more succinct and readable.
        Returns:
        a new listIndex-specific EqualsExpressionFactory instance, to be used to construct a criterion when building an OrganizationAccountStoreMappingCriteria query.
